From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Buildroot <buildroot@buildroot.org>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] tools: make materialeditor optional when Qt::Network is absent

materialeditor uses QLocalSocket/QLocalServer from QtNetwork. Guard it
the same way balsamui is guarded on Qt::Widgets, so host builds with
-DFEATURE_network=OFF do not fail.

This mirrors what upstream Qt did after 6.4.x.

Signed-off-by: Buildroot <buildroot@buildroot.org>
---
 tools/CMakeLists.txt | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/tools/CMakeLists.txt b/tools/CMakeLists.txt
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/tools/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/tools/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -14,4 +14,8 @@
 endif()
 add_subdirectory(instancer)
 add_subdirectory(shapegen)
-add_subdirectory(materialeditor)
+if(TARGET Qt::Network)
+    add_subdirectory(materialeditor)
+else()
+    message(NOTICE "Skipping materialeditor as the condition \"TARGET Qt::Network\" is not met.")
+endif()
